	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=150661"><span id=" ">Callawayn</span></a><br /><span id="notbold">87 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Good [3.90]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>For the low-level players that are searching this site and drooling over this item, don't worry about saving your pp to buy this robe.&nbsp;&nbsp;By the time you reach your fifties and you're in a decent guild, you'll get several opportunities to get this robe, or some that kick this robe's butt.<br/><br/>If you're in Fear, and this robe drops, you'll probably want to roll for it.  However, if you've got a PoG raid upcoming, you might want to pass, because better robes drop there.  <br/><br/>If you won this robe on the Fear raid, your guild leaders might not let you roll on a PoG robe, which only has one less INT, nearly twice the mana and hp's, +5 to all resists, and a mana-free right clickable spell.  You tell me which you'd rather have?<br/><br/>Sure, this is an upgrade to your Froggy, Netted Kelp, or Jumpy robe, but there are better ones out there that whomp on this robe, and are just as easy (if you consider Plane's mobs easy) to get.<br/><br/>Work on your levels, and save your PP.  Don't worry about having to buy it.  Eventually, you'll get this or a better robe.  Save your PP for Sunstrike or KEI, which is going to cost you 20-30k, unless your guild decides to take down the mobs that drop the scrolls. <br/><br/>Nestefus Nucallodem<br/>Lvl 56 Evoker<br/>House of Elder - Tarrew Marr<br/>Proud Wearer of a Sorcerer's Robe from PoG<br/></p>&nbsp;<br /><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br /><br/></td></tr>
